<TITLE> 3 to be grilled for suspicious activities </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 11 (bdnews24.com)  Three men were remanded into police custody Thursday for questioning over activities surrounding the BDR mutiny. Retired BDR Subedar Hajee Torab Ali and Prime Coaching Centre owner Zakir Hossain were arrested by Hazaribagh police 'on suspicion' under Section 54 of the CPrC. Hazaribagh police sub-inspector Kazi Rabiul Huq said Torab, an executive of the BDR Welfare Association, along with Zakir, son of a BDR man, composed leaflets that were distributed in Darbar Hall on the day of the mutiny. A civilian named Mizanur Rahman was arrested by Lalbagh police for allegedly taking part in a controversial rally in support of the BDR jawans on the first day of the mutiny. Magistrate Moazzem Hossain of Dhaka CMM Court on Thursday gave Hazaribagh police two days to grill Toraba and Zakir, and Lalbagh police three days to question Mizanur. Meanwhile, metropolitan magistrate Saifur Rahman Siddique ordered BDR Sepoy Moniruzzaman, arrested under Section 54 by Gulshan police, to jail. bd
